  "original_title": "22\u0d9a\u0da7 \u0d91\u0dbb\u0dd9\u0dc4\u0dd2\u0dc0 \u0db4\u0dd9\u0dad\u0dca\u0dc3\u0db8\u0dca \u0db1\u0dc0\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Nine petitions against 22",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "9 petitions have been filed before the Supreme Court today (18) stating that certain clauses of the 22nd Constitutional Amendment Bill are contrary to the Constitution and requesting an order to pass it by a special number of MPs and a referendum, including Dr. Gunadasa Amarasekara.",
        "These petitions have been filed before the Supreme Court by 9 people, including Dr. Gunadasa Amarasekara, General Secretary of Praideh Peramuna, lawyer Nagananda Kodithuvakku, and lawyer Nuvan Bellantudawe.",
        "The petitioners have pointed out in their petition that the Twenty-second Constitution Amendment Bill has been included in the parliamentary agenda on the 10th and some of its clauses are against the Constitution.",
        "Therefore, the petitioners request in their petitions to issue an order to pass this subject to the approval of a special majority group of members of Parliament and through a referendum."
      ],
